The paper deals with algorithms that aim to increase representation of historically disadvantaged populations, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of integer linear programs to formalize optimization problems is also a common technique in these fields. The paper also deals with sensitive attributes, which is a topic in the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and privacy (cs.CY). Finally, the experimental evaluation and quantification of trade-offs is a common technique in the field of social computing (cs.SI).
